            <article>
                <h2>Ice cream</h2>
                <p>Ice cream is a sweet, frozen dessert made from a base of milk, cream, sugar, and flavorings, churned while freezing to incorporate air and create a smooth, semi-solid foam with tiny ice crystals. To be legally called ice cream in the U.S., it must contain at least 10% milkfat, contributing to its rich texture, with common additions like fruits, nuts, or chocolate for variety. </p>
                <figure>
                    <img width="50%" src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQYFULypZgudRiujz0RZgtiT5R7Z2rilcdcBQ&s">
                    <figcaption>ICE CREAM</figcaption>
